    "photo": "Mehmet_Aktaş.jpg",
    "bullets": [
      "Associate Professor School of Data Science and Analytics College of Computing and Software Engineering Kennesaw State University"
    ],
    "story": "<p>I am an associate professor in the School of Data Science and Analytics at Kennesaw State \nUniversity - College of Computing and Software Engineering. My primary research focus is machine learning and data \nscience, specifically focusing on network science. I am particularly interested in utilizing topological data analysis \n(TDA) tools to address challenges in network matching and influence maximization problems and their applications in social, \nbiological, and business networks. I received my Ph.D. from the Department of Mathematics at Florida State University, \nunder the supervision of Eriko Hironaka. I received my MS in 2011 from the Department of Mathematics at the Bilkent \nUniversity working with Alex Degtyarev. </p>",
